==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Confiner
<hw>Con*fin"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, limits or restrains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confiner</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Confiner
<hw>Con"fi`ner</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ <?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
lives on confines, or near the border of a country; a borderer; a near
neighbor.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Happy <qex>confiners</qex> you of other lands,⟦br⟧
That shift your soil, and oft 'scape tyrants' hands.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confinity</ent>⟦br⟧
